The paper deals with the analysis of communication systems in parallel fading channels, which is a topic closely related to information theory and communication theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of large deviations theory and Meijer's G-function, which are mathematical tools commonly used in network information theory and stochastic systems, suggesting that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between transmission reliability and efficiency, which is a topic relevant to control theory and system engineering, indicating that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category.
